{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17654756","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17654756"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:54:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:54:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18628"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18628","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18628"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11360"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76504"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11360","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11360"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18628"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62001"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10272"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26366"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26369"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76504","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76504"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA skeletal muscle fibre undergoes a twitch contraction in response to a single action potential. The response can be divided into distinct temporal phases.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the sequence of events during a muscle twitch contraction?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Latent period, contraction phase, relaxation phase","Contraction phase, relaxation phase, latent period","Contraction phase, latent period, relaxation phase","Relaxation phase, latent period, contraction phase","Latent period, relaxation phase, contraction phase"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct sequence is \u003Cstrong\u003Elatent period, contraction phase, relaxation phase\u003C/strong\u003E. During the latent period (2-3 ms), action potentials trigger calcium release from the sarcoplasmic reticulum, but no physical shortening occurs yet. The contraction phase follows as cross-bridges cycle and generate force. Finally, the relaxation phase occurs as calcium is actively pumped back into the sarcoplasmic reticulum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect sequences can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELatent period, relaxation phase, contraction phase\u003C/strong\u003E - Relaxation cannot occur before contraction\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContraction phase, latent period, relaxation phase\u003C/strong\u003E - The latent period must precede contraction\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERelaxation phase, latent period, contraction phase\u003C/strong\u003E - Relaxation can only occur after contraction\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContraction phase, relaxation phase, latent period\u003C/strong\u003E - The latent period is always the first phase\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis sequence ensures orderly excitation-contraction coupling and subsequent muscle relaxation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A twitch contraction is a single muscle contraction-relaxation cycle in response to a single action potential.","The latent period represents the time between stimulation and the start of contraction, during which calcium is being released.","The contraction phase involves cross-bridge cycling and force generation, while the relaxation phase involves active calcium reuptake."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. 